main event: An unidentified flying object was observed near Kirtland AFB in New Mexico on November 1, 1953.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 7 minutes., The object was detected both visually and by radar., There were no photographs or physical evidence associated with the sighting., The number of objects observed were categorized as CIG, with a fitting of 1-3., The observation occurred at a military base known for UFO investigations.
